    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "James",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 4,
        "summary": "Wars are born of lusts\u2014The friends of the world are the enemies of God\u2014Sin is failure to walk in the light we have received.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "From whence come wars and fightings among you? come they not hence, even of your lusts that war in your members?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0War.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of the Early Christian Church.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0pleasures, gratifications, passions.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye lust, and have not: ye kill, and desire to have, and cannot obtain: ye fight and war, yet ye have not, because ye ask not.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye ask, and receive not, because ye ask amiss, that ye may consume it upon your lusts.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prayer.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 10:5 (4\u20136).",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0wickedly, wrongly. Rom. 8:26 (26\u201327); D&C 46:30 (28\u201330); 88:65 (64\u201365).",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0waste, expend. D&C 46:9.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lust.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye adulterers and adulteresses, know ye not that the friendship of the world is enmity with God? whosoever therefore will be a friend of the world is the enemy of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Whore.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0World; Worldliness.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 76
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Opposition.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 86
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Enemies.",
                        "start": 154,
                        "end": 159
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1542
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Do ye think that the scripture saith in vain, The spirit that dwelleth in us lusteth to envy?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Envy.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But he giveth more grace. Wherefore he saith, God resisteth the proud, but giveth grace unto the humble.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Grace.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Pride.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Poor in Spirit.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Submit yourselves therefore to God. Resist the devil, and he will flee from you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reconciliation; Submissiveness.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abstain; Self-Mastery.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Devil.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Draw nigh to God, and he will draw nigh to you. Cleanse your hands, ye sinners; and purify your hearts, ye double minded.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Presence of.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 69:18; D&C 88:63.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Repent.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Purification; Purity.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 95
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Be afflicted, and mourn, and weep: let your laughter be turned to mourning, and your joy to heaviness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0Endure hardship, Suffer harassment.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 22:12; Joel 2:17; 2\u00a0Cor. 7:10.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mourning.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Humble yourselves in the sight of the Lord, and he shall lift you up.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contrite Heart; Humility.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Speak not evil one of another, brethren. He that speaketh evil of his brother, and judgeth his brother, speaketh evil of the law, and judgeth the law: but if thou judge the law, thou art not a doer of the law, but a judge.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gossip.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Citizenship.",
                        "start": 125,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "There is one lawgiver, who is able to save and to destroy: who art thou that judgest another?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Morm. 8:20 (19\u201320).",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Go to now, ye that say, To day or to morrow we will go into such a city, and continue there a year, and buy and sell, and get gain:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 27:1.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Whereas ye know not what shall be on the morrow. For what is your life? It is even a vapour, that appeareth for a little time, and then vanisheth away.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 7:31 (29\u201331); Jacob 7:26.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For that ye ought to say, If the Lord will, we shall live, and do this, or that.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But now ye rejoice in your boastings: all such rejoicing is evil.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Boast.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore to him that knoweth to do good, and doeth it not, to him it is sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 12:47; 2\u00a0Ne. 9:25 (25\u201327).",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Disobedience; Good Works; Obedience.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}